Bayern Munich, on Saturday, extended their record of successive league wins with a sixth straight Bundesliga title and 28 overall after overcoming their Bavarian rivals, Ausburg, 4-1. Four players made it happen in the tensed match as Bayern came from behind to snatch the win and open up a 20-point gap ahead of Schalke with five rounds of matches to go in the season.
Corentino Tolisso, James Rodriguez, Arjen Robben and Sandro Wagner all scored in the match to hand the Bavarian giants a massive 4-1 win at the WWK Arena.
Meanwhile, the treble-chasing Bavarians rested a host of players with Wednesday’s Champions League quarter-final second leg tie against Sevilla in mind. Robert Lewandowski, Thomas Muller, Thiago, Franck Ribery, Mats Hummels and Javi Martinez were all on the bench. Also on the bench were David Alaba and Arturo Vidal.
Bayern Munich seemed to have been in trouble when Sven Ulreich’s parried save hit Sule and flew into their own net. But Tolisso headed in Joshua Kimmich’s cross and Rodriguez then smashed home from close range.
